<div class='p4'>
<h2>Measure</h2>



<p>Measure refers to the length of a line of text. It is one of the most important aspects of readability.</p>
<blockquote class='m0 lh-copy measure-wide pl4 bl bw3'>
  <p>
  “Anything from 45 to 75 characters is widely regarded as a satisfactory length of line for a single-column page… the 66-character line (counting both letters and spaces) is widely regarded as ideal. For multiple-column work, a better average is 40-50 characters.” 
  </p>
  <p class='b gray-0'>—Robert Bringhurst, The Elements of Typographic Style</p>
</blockquote>
        
</div>
  <section class='p4'>
    <h3>Sizes</h3>
    <p>
    Tachyons provides 3 classes for setting measure.
    </p>
<pre>
<code>
.measure = line lengths ~66 characters
.measure-narrow = line lengths ~45 characters
.measure-wide = line lengths ~80 characters
</code>
</pre>
    
  </section>
